verses:
Unto the end, in praises, a psalm for Asaph:  a canticle to the
Assyrians.
In Judea God is known:  his name is great in Israel.
And his place is in peace:  and his abode in Sion:

There hath he broken the powers of bows, the shield, the sword,
and the battle.
Thou enlightenest wonderfully from the everlasting hills.

All the foolish of heart were troubled.  They have slept their
sleep; and all the men of riches have found nothing in their hands.

At thy rebuke, O God of Jacob, they have all slumbered that
mounted on horseback.

Thou art terrible, and who shall resist thee?  from that time thy
wrath.

Thou hast caused judgment to be heard from heaven:  the earth
trembled and was still,
When God arose in judgment, to save all the meek of the earth.

For the thought of man shall give praise to thee:  and the
remainders of the thought shall keep holiday to thee.

Vow ye, and pay to the Lord your God:  all you that are round
about him bring presents.  To him that is terrible,

Even to him who taketh away the spirit of princes:  to the
terrible with the kings of the earth.
